(fetchWidth, area_cell_area).explanation: Increasing fetch width requires more parallel fetch logic and wider datapaths, directly increasing the physical area needed for cell placement;

(fetchWidth, power_register).explanation: Wider fetch requires more registers to buffer the additional instructions fetched per cycle, directly increasing register file power consumption;

(fetchWidth, nL2TLBEntries).explanation: Fetch width affects instruction fetch rate while L2 TLB entries are determined by memory subsystem design requirements independently;
